1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,760
Think twice before connecting to that free public Wi-Fi.

2
00:00:03,760 --> 00:00:08,000
It might seem convenient, but it's often a digital minefield.

3
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:11,200
Public networks are usually unsecured.

4
00:00:11,200 --> 00:00:15,360
This means hackers can easily snoop on your internet activity.

5
00:00:15,360 --> 00:00:18,240
They can see what websites you visit.

6
00:00:18,240 --> 00:00:21,440
They can even steal your login details.

7
00:00:21,440 --> 00:00:24,880
Some criminals create fake Wi-Fi hotspots.

8
00:00:24,880 --> 00:00:28,480
They look legitimate, like free airport Wi-Fi.

9
00:00:28,480 --> 00:00:32,320
But once you connect, they gain access to your device.

10
00:00:32,320 --> 00:00:36,720
Your passwords, bank details, and personal photos are all at risk.

11
00:00:36,720 --> 00:00:41,440
Imagine someone accessing your social media or emptying your bank account.

12
00:00:41,440 --> 00:00:45,040
It's like leaving your front door wide open for thieves.

13
00:00:45,040 --> 00:00:46,880
So, here's your practical tip.

14
00:00:46,880 --> 00:00:52,880
Always use a virtual private network, or VPN, or stick to your cellular data when you're out.

